{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784347472075,"sessionID":"ses_08c9e6f24ffeeO094AtRujB8OZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_8ded8a196ecc4cb580fdcbee","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"echo \"=== smart_routing.md template ===\" && cat .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md 2>&1 | head -80 && echo \"=== skill_advisor deep routing grep ===\" && rg -n \"_apply_deep_skill_routing_layer|has_deep_signal|DEEP_ROUTING_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD\" .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py 2>&1 | head -30","workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse"},"output":"=== smart_routing.md template ===\n---\ntitle: Skill Smart Router - Resilience Pattern\ndescription: Canonical resilient smart-router pattern for skill resource discovery, guarded loading, runtime routing keys, and graceful fallback.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"skill smart router\"\n  - \"resilient resource discovery\"\n  - \"guarded reference loading\"\n  - \"router fallback pattern\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.8.0.3\n---\n\n# Skill Smart Router - Resilience Pattern\n\nCopy-paste pseudocode patterns that make a skill's smart router survive reference and asset changes (renames, deletes, new project folders, missing files) without crashing or silently degrading.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nSmart routers fail when resource paths drift, reference folders are deleted, static file lists go stale, or routing logic assumes one hardcoded project or mode forever. This asset packages the canonical four-pattern fix: every routing call discovers the current markdown inventory, guards paths inside the skill folder, loads only files that still exist, selects resources from a runtime-derived routing key, and returns useful fallback guidance instead of crashing or silently loading nothing.\n\n### Usage\n\nCopy the four pseudocode patterns from §2 into your skill's SMART ROUTING section. Adapt the routing key (e.g., git remote → project; intent label → workflow; stack marker → tooling; env var → runtime mode) per §3 Generalization Guide. Preserve your skill's domain-specific `INTENT_MODEL`, `RESOURCE_MAP`, and load levels — only swap the **discovery + load + fallback** mechanics. Apply the structural safeguards from §4 to every router-driven `load()` call. Audit your draft against §5 Anti-Patterns before merging.\n\n---\n\n## 2. THE 4 PATTERNS\n\n### Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Discover routable markdown at every routing call\n- Do not maintain static lists of every reference or asset file\n- Recursive `rglob(\"*.md\")` under `references/` and `assets/`\n\n**Template:**\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\nRESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\n\ndef discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:\n    docs = []\n    for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n        if base.exists():\n            docs.extend(path for path in base.rglob(\"*.md\") if path.is_file())\n    return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}\n```\n\n### Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Guard each path against the discovered inventory before loading\n- Suppress duplicate loads via a `seen` set\n- Missing files just don't load; no crash\n\n**Template:**\n\n```python\nloaded = []\nseen = set()\ninventory = discover_markdown_resources()\n\ndef load_if_available(relative_path: str) -> None:\n    guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n    if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n        load(guarded)\n        loaded.append(guarded)\n        seen.add(guarded)\n```\n\n### Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Routing key derives from a runtime signal (git remote, intent label, stack marker, env var, command, task field)\n=== skill_advisor deep routing grep ===\n709:        _apply_deep_skill_routing_layer(recommendations, prompt)\n2572:DEEP_ROUTING_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.65\n2810:    if max_score < DEEP_ROUTING_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD:\n2815:def _apply_deep_skill_routing_layer(\n2825:    has_deep_signal = re.search(\n2829:    if not has_deep_signal:\n4009:    _apply_deep_skill_routing_layer(recommendations, prompt)\n","metadata":{"output":"=== smart_routing.md template ===\n---\ntitle: Skill Smart Router - Resilience Pattern\ndescription: Canonical resilient smart-router pattern for skill resource discovery, guarded loading, runtime routing keys, and graceful fallback.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"skill smart router\"\n  - \"resilient resource discovery\"\n  - \"guarded reference loading\"\n  - \"router fallback pattern\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.8.0.3\n---\n\n# Skill Smart Router - Resilience Pattern\n\nCopy-paste pseudocode patterns that make a skill's smart router survive reference and asset changes (renames, deletes, new project folders, missing files) without crashing or silently degrading.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nSmart routers fail when resource paths drift, reference folders are deleted, static file lists go stale, or routing logic assumes one hardcoded project or mode forever. This asset packages the canonical four-pattern fix: every routing call discovers the current markdown inventory, guards paths inside the skill folder, loads only files that still exist, selects resources from a runtime-derived routing key, and returns useful fallback guidance instead of crashing or silently loading nothing.\n\n### Usage\n\nCopy the four pseudocode patterns from §2 into your skill's SMART ROUTING section. Adapt the routing key (e.g., git remote → project; intent label → workflow; stack marker → tooling; env var → runtime mode) per §3 Generalization Guide. Preserve your skill's domain-specific `INTENT_MODEL`, `RESOURCE_MAP`, and load levels — only swap the **discovery + load + fallback** mechanics. Apply the structural safeguards from §4 to every router-driven `load()` call. Audit your draft against §5 Anti-Patterns before merging.\n\n---\n\n## 2. THE 4 PATTERNS\n\n### Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Discover routable markdown at every routing call\n- Do not maintain static lists of every reference or asset file\n- Recursive `rglob(\"*.md\")` under `references/` and `assets/`\n\n**Template:**\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\nRESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\n\ndef discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:\n    docs = []\n    for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n        if base.exists():\n            docs.extend(path for path in base.rglob(\"*.md\") if path.is_file())\n    return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}\n```\n\n### Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Guard each path against the discovered inventory before loading\n- Suppress duplicate loads via a `seen` set\n- Missing files just don't load; no crash\n\n**Template:**\n\n```python\nloaded = []\nseen = set()\ninventory = discover_markdown_resources()\n\ndef load_if_available(relative_path: str) -> None:\n    guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n    if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n        load(guarded)\n        loaded.append(guarded)\n        seen.add(guarded)\n```\n\n### Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Routing key derives from a runtime signal (git remote, intent label, stack marker, env var, command, task field)\n=== skill_advisor deep routing grep ===\n709:        _apply_deep_skill_routing_layer(recommendations, prompt)\n2572:DEEP_ROUTING_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.65\n2810:    if max_score < DEEP_ROUTING_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD:\n2815:def _apply_deep_skill_routing_layer(\n2825:    has_deep_signal = re.search(\n2829:    if not has_deep_signal:\n4009:    _apply_deep_skill_routing_layer(recommendations, prompt)\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"echo \"=== smart_routing.md template ===\" && cat .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md 2>&1 | head -80 && echo \"=== skill_advisor deep routing grep ===\" && rg -n \"_apply_deep_skill_routing_layer|has_deep_signal|DEEP_ROUTING_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD\" .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py 2>&1 | head -30","time":{"start":1784347472072,"end":1784347472074}},"id":"prt_f7365b0b80017k21hgUGJfJBXZ","sessionID":"ses_08c9e6f24ffeeO094AtRujB8OZ","messageID":"msg_f73659384001Ess5fuTYv50vUs"}}
