{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784347968019,"sessionID":"ses_08c9e6f24ffeeO094AtRujB8OZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_431ac60497224ebf84d0808a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"newInfoRatio\":0.80,\"status\":\"insight\",\"focus\":\"Cross-domain analogies — load-balancer health-check transfer (agenda #3)\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"keyQuestions\":[\"q2\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"q2\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-18T06:18:00Z\",\"durationMs\":540000,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\",\"lineage\":\"glm-oob\"}}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f1-collapse\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"label\":\"Four of five analogies collapse to weighted selection or bundleRules; only load-balancer health-check and DNS TTL add a new primitive\",\"iteration\":2,\"sources\":[\"hub-router.json (every weight=4)\",\"021/run2-archive/research.md thread G A3\"]}\n{\"type\":\"claim\",\"id\":\"f2-health\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"label\":\"Each mode has a runtime health score; routing weight = staticWeight × healthMultiplier\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f3-costs\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"label\":\"Four structural costs health-check hides: prompt-dependent state, grader cost, cold-start, Goodhart\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f4-feedback\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"label\":\"The genuine transfer is the feedback channel (routeId + re-prompt signal), smaller than the health-check analogy\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"claim\",\"id\":\"f5-reframe\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"label\":\"Closed-loop routing supplies the measurement infrastructure run-2 said was missing\",\"iteration\":2,\"sources\":[\"021/run2-archive/research.md thread D\"]}\n{\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"e-q2-f4\",\"relation\":\"ANSWERS\",\"source\":\"f4-feedback\",\"target\":\"q2\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"e-f2-f4\",\"relation\":\"SUPERSEDES\",\"source\":\"f4-feedback\",\"target\":\"f2-health\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"e-f4-f5\",\"relation\":\"DERIVED_FROM\",\"source\":\"f5-reframe\",\"target\":\"f4-feedback\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"direction\":\"OS scheduler priority/preemption as a routing primitive\",\"reason\":\"Priority=today's weight; preemption incoherent for one-shot routing; aging collapses to learned weights\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"direction\":\"IP longest-prefix match as a routing primitive\",\"reason\":\"vocabularyClasses already is longest-prefix match by another name\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"direction\":\"Receptionist ask-don't-guess as a routing primitive\",\"reason\":\"Already shipped as defer; triage protocol is bundleRules\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"direction\":\"Full health-score routing as immediate destination\",\"reason\":\"F3 four costs make it multi-release, not refactor\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"observation\",\"id\":\"obs-iter002-handoff-typed-signal\",\"packet\":\"023\",\"classification\":\"real\",\"iteration\":2,\"note\":\"Handoff is a typed closed-loop signal; strictly more informative than re-prompt. Iteration 3 should stress handoff as the primitive, not just as a way to dissolve keep-vs-null.\"}\n{\"type\":\"idea_observed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":2,\"ideaId\":\"idea-closed-loop-router\",\"idea\":\"Closed-loop routing: emit routeId, record whether the next operator turn re-enters the router; this is the minimal feedback channel\",\"category\":\"ideas\",\"source\":\"iteration-002.md\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-18T06:18:30Z\"}\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/023-oob-glm-parallel/research/lineages/glm-oob/deltas/iter-002.jsonl"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/023-oob-glm-parallel/research/lineages/glm-oob/deltas/iter-002.jsonl","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/023-oob-glm-parallel/research/lineages/glm-oob/deltas/iter-002.jsonl","time":{"start":1784347968015,"end":1784347968018}},"id":"prt_f736d420d001USsrf8oFCgHFRw","sessionID":"ses_08c9e6f24ffeeO094AtRujB8OZ","messageID":"msg_f736cf73f001WlC64ZDe38Zi00"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1784347968718,"sessionID":"ses_08c9e6f24ffeeO094AtRujB8OZ","part":{"id":"prt_f736d44cc001yQJAhl5Ff7sD4r","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"9964cb590f0385b3279b01a130bb9ba5c08f8b69","messageID":"msg_f736cf73f001WlC64ZDe38Zi00","sessionID":"ses_08c9e6f24ffeeO094AtRujB8OZ","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":91169,"input":799,"output":898,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":89472}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1784348006420,"sessionID":"ses_08c9e6f24ffeeO094AtRujB8OZ","part":{"id":"prt_f736dd8090010cqcYK2pEWIswv","messageID":"msg_f736d471e001Lbg9xVvF9As9TL","sessionID":"ses_08c9e6f24ffeeO094AtRujB8OZ","snapshot":"9964cb590f0385b3279b01a130bb9ba5c08f8b69","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784348006424,"sessionID":"ses_08c9e6f24ffeeO094AtRujB8OZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_912b965e9b764f649a402199","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/023-oob-glm-parallel/research/lineages/glm-oob/deep-research-strategy.md","newString":"## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n\n- **q1 — If Layer-1 routing were deleted entirely, what breaks vs improves?** (answered, iteration 1)\n  - Reframed: abolition is a **tier-split** (cold advisor decides `skill`; hot advisor-loaded vocab decides `mode`), not a deletion.\n  - Breaks: vocabulary centralisation kills per-skill authoring boundary; advisor becomes Layer-0+1 coupled; eager resource selection forced; `bundleRules` lose their encoding home.\n  - Improves: keep-vs-null disappears at the root; drift detectable at one file; `clarifying_question` already shipped becomes the single disambiguation surface.\n- **q2 — Which routing primitive transfers from a non-routing domain, and at what cost?** (answered, iteration 2)\n  - Four of five analogies (OS scheduler, IP longest-prefix, DNS hierarchy, receptionist) collapse to weighted-selection / bundleRules / defer — already shipped.\n  - The genuine transfer is the **feedback channel** itself: closed-loop routing (emit `routeId`, record re-prompt). Load-balancer health-check and DNS TTL both pointed at it via different routes.\n  - Health-score routing (F2) is the multi-release destination, not the immediate next step; F3's four costs (prompt-dependent state, grader cost, cold-start, Goodhart) make it non-trivial.\n\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n\n- **Reading the one shipped precedent (`_apply_deep_skill_routing_layer`)** made abolition answerable from evidence rather than speculation — it is the in-advisor hot tier already (iteration 1, F1).\n- **Pushing to the literal deletion** surfaced the tier-split reframe (F4) instead of stalling at \"null everyone.\"\n- **Stress-testing for second-order costs** (F2) produced four concrete breakages the run-1/run-2 study did not name.\n- **Surveying all five analogies before committing to one** (iteration 2, F1) produced the negative-knowledge finding that four-of-five collapse; the one that does not (feedback channel) is itself a smaller primitive than its source analogy suggested.\n\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n\n- **Searching for a \"minimal deletion\"** — none exists. Keeping any of `routerPolicy` / `routerSignals` / `bundleRules` / `defaultResource` re-invents a Layer-1 router. The radical answer is all-or-nothing.\n- **Trying to make the load-balancer transfer literal** (iter 2, F2) — the state-space explosion (F3.1) killed it as an immediate design.\n\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n\n- **Static-selection analogies as a source of routing primitives.** OS scheduler, IP longest-prefix, receptionist — all collapse to today's `weight` / `vocabularyClasses` / `defer` / `bundleRules`. (iteration 2)\n\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n- **\"Set every `defaultMode` to null\" as abolition** — run-1/run-2 answer wearing a wig; abolition only counts if the four other routerPolicy fields are also deleted. (iteration 1)\n- **\"Generalise `_apply_deep_skill_routing_layer` verbatim\"** — lexical regex works for deep-loops only because their trigger vocab is small and stable; per-hub regex per domain is the distributed monolith in another shape. (iteration 1)\n- **OS scheduler priority/preemption** — incoherent for one-shot routing; aging collapses to learned weights. (iteration 2)\n- **IP longest-prefix match** — `vocabularyClasses` already is this. (iteration 2)\n- **Receptionist \"ask, don't guess\"** — already shipped as `defer`. (iteration 2)\n- **Full health-score routing (F2) as the immediate destination** — F3's four costs make it multi-release. The feedback-channel bridge (F4) is the productive next step. (iteration 2)\n\n## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Saturated: static-selection analogies (4-of-5 agenda-#3 candidates exhausted)\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: agenda #2, #4, #5, #6, #7, #8 open; #1 explored (tier-split); #3 explored (feedback channel)\n- Promoted ideas: `idea-closed-loop-router` (1 observation, threshold 2 not yet met)\n\n## 11. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n\n- **CF1 (seed for iter 3):** abolition makes the advisor the single deferrer, but advisor deferral is a *clarifying-question*, not a *handoff*. Is deferral the right primitive, or is handoff? (from iteration 1, obs-iter001-handoff-seed)\n- **CF2 (seed for iter 4):** the tier-split reframe implies the advisor does both layers — what is the advisor's confidence story under that load? (from iteration 1, F4)\n- **CF3 (seed for iter 3 + iter 4, NEW):** handoff is a *typed* closed-loop signal — strictly more informative than re-prompt (from iteration 2, obs-iter002-handoff-typed-signal). Iteration 3 should stress handoff as a primitive; iteration 4 should treat handoff as the input to a learned router.\n\n## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n**Iteration 3: No-wrong-door / handoff routing + routing as dialogue (agenda #4 + #5).**\nCF1 + CF3 converge here: if any mode could accept any request and then hand off (typed transfer),\ndoes the keep-vs-null distinction dissolve? And does handoff supply the closed-loop signal F4 needs?\nThe lateral claim to stress-test: routing stops being \"pick the right mode upfront\" and becomes\n\"any mode accepts, then types the transfer.\" The zero-signal case is not a silent default and not\na clarification dialog — it is a one-turn typed negotiation.","oldString":"## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n\n- **q1 — If Layer-1 routing were deleted entirely, what breaks vs improves?** (answered, iteration 1)\n  - Reframed: abolition is a **tier-split** (cold advisor decides `skill`; hot advisor-loaded vocab decides `mode`), not a deletion.\n  - Breaks: vocabulary centralisation kills per-skill authoring boundary; advisor becomes Layer-0+1 coupled; eager resource selection forced; `bundleRules` lose their encoding home.\n  - Improves: keep-vs-null disappears at the root; drift detectable at one file; `clarifying_question` already shipped becomes the single disambiguation surface.\n\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n\n- **Reading the one shipped precedent (`_apply_deep_skill_routing_layer`)** made abolition answerable from evidence rather than speculation — it is the in-advisor hot tier already (iteration 1, F1).\n- **Pushing to the literal deletion** surfaced the tier-split reframe (F4) instead of stalling at \"null everyone.\"\n- **Stress-testing for second-order costs** (F2) produced four concrete breakages the run-1/run-2 study did not name.\n\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n\n- **Searching for a \"minimal deletion\"** — none exists. Keeping any of `routerPolicy` / `routerSignals` / `bundleRules` / `defaultResource` re-invents a Layer-1 router. The radical answer is all-or-nothing.\n\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n\n(none yet)\n\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n- **\"Set every `defaultMode` to null\" as abolition** — run-1/run-2 answer wearing a wig; abolition only counts if the four other routerPolicy fields are also deleted. (iteration 1)\n- **\"Generalise `_apply_deep_skill_routing_layer` verbatim\"** — lexical regex works for deep-loops only because their trigger vocab is small and stable; per-hub regex per domain is the distributed monolith in another shape. (iteration 1)\n\n## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Saturated: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: agenda items #2–#8 open; #1 explored (tier-split reframe)\n\n## 11. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n\n- **CF1 (seed for iter 3):** abolition makes the advisor the single deferrer, but advisor deferral is a *clarifying-question*, not a *handoff*. Is deferral the right primitive, or is handoff? (from iteration 1, obs-iter001-handoff-seed)\n- **CF2 (seed for iter 4):** the tier-split reframe implies the advisor does both layers — what is the advisor's confidence story under that load? (from iteration 1, F4)\n\n## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n**Iteration 2: Cross-domain analogies — the load-balancer health-check transfer (agenda #3).**\nIteration 1 stayed inside the routing domain. Iteration 2 deliberately imports a primitive from\noutside routing entirely: weighted round-robin with health checks. Stress-test the lateral claim:\nwhat if every mode had a runtime health score (recent success rate, recent token cost) and routing\nweight adapted to it? Today every weight is static (`\"weight\": 4` everywhere). The load-balancer\nanalogy is the one most likely to surface a primitive routing doesn't have — OS scheduler, DNS,\nand IP-router analogies collapse back to \"weighted selection\" and add less."},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/023-oob-glm-parallel/research/lineages/glm-oob/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/023-oob-glm-parallel/research/lineages/glm-oob/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/023-oob-glm-parallel/research/lineages/glm-oob/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -84,48 +84,59 @@\n - **q1 — If Layer-1 routing were deleted entirely, what breaks vs improves?** (answered, iteration 1)\n   - Reframed: abolition is a **tier-split** (cold advisor decides `skill`; hot advisor-loaded vocab decides `mode`), not a deletion.\n   - Breaks: vocabulary centralisation kills per-skill authoring boundary; advisor becomes Layer-0+1 coupled; eager resource selection forced; `bundleRules` lose their encoding home.\n   - Improves: keep-vs-null disappears at the root; drift detectable at one file; `clarifying_question` already shipped becomes the single disambiguation surface.\n+- **q2 — Which routing primitive transfers from a non-routing domain, and at what cost?** (answered, iteration 2)\n+  - Four of five analogies (OS scheduler, IP longest-prefix, DNS hierarchy, receptionist) collapse to weighted-selection / bundleRules / defer — already shipped.\n+  - The genuine transfer is the **feedback channel** itself: closed-loop routing (emit `routeId`, record re-prompt). Load-balancer health-check and DNS TTL both pointed at it via different routes.\n+  - Health-score routing (F2) is the multi-release destination, not the immediate next step; F3's four costs (prompt-dependent state, grader cost, cold-start, Goodhart) make it non-trivial.\n \n ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n \n - **Reading the one shipped precedent (`_apply_deep_skill_routing_layer`)** made abolition answerable from evidence rather than speculation — it is the in-advisor hot tier already (iteration 1, F1).\n - **Pushing to the literal deletion** surfaced the tier-split reframe (F4) instead of stalling at \"null everyone.\"\n - **Stress-testing for second-order costs** (F2) produced four concrete breakages the run-1/run-2 study did not name.\n+- **Surveying all five analogies before committing to one** (iteration 2, F1) produced the negative-knowledge finding that four-of-five collapse; the one that does not (feedback channel) is itself a smaller primitive than its source analogy suggested.\n \n ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n \n - **Searching for a \"minimal deletion\"** — none exists. Keeping any of `routerPolicy` / `routerSignals` / `bundleRules` / `defaultResource` re-invents a Layer-1 router. The radical answer is all-or-nothing.\n+- **Trying to make the load-balancer transfer literal** (iter 2, F2) — the state-space explosion (F3.1) killed it as an immediate design.\n \n ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n \n-(none yet)\n+- **Static-selection analogies as a source of routing primitives.** OS scheduler, IP longest-prefix, receptionist — all collapse to today's `weight` / `vocabularyClasses` / `defer` / `bundleRules`. (iteration 2)\n \n ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n \n - **\"Set every `defaultMode` to null\" as abolition** — run-1/run-2 answer wearing a wig; abolition only counts if the four other routerPolicy fields are also deleted. (iteration 1)\n - **\"Generalise `_apply_deep_skill_routing_layer` verbatim\"** — lexical regex works for deep-loops only because their trigger vocab is small and stable; per-hub regex per domain is the distributed monolith in another shape. (iteration 1)\n+- **OS scheduler priority/preemption** — incoherent for one-shot routing; aging collapses to learned weights. (iteration 2)\n+- **IP longest-prefix match** — `vocabularyClasses` already is this. (iteration 2)\n+- **Receptionist \"ask, don't guess\"** — already shipped as `defer`. (iteration 2)\n+- **Full health-score routing (F2) as the immediate destination** — F3's four costs make it multi-release. The feedback-channel bridge (F4) is the productive next step. (iteration 2)\n \n ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n - Completed pivots: 0\n - Failed pivots: 0\n-- Saturated: none yet\n+- Saturated: static-selection analogies (4-of-5 agenda-#3 candidates exhausted)\n - Pivot lineage: none yet\n-- Remaining frontier: agenda items #2–#8 open; #1 explored (tier-split reframe)\n+- Remaining frontier: agenda #2, #4, #5, #6, #7, #8 open; #1 explored (tier-split); #3 explored (feedback channel)\n+- Promoted ideas: `idea-closed-loop-router` (1 observation, threshold 2 not yet met)\n \n ## 11. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n \n - **CF1 (seed for iter 3):** abolition makes the advisor the single deferrer, but advisor deferral is a *clarifying-question*, not a *handoff*. Is deferral the right primitive, or is handoff? (from iteration 1, obs-iter001-handoff-seed)\n - **CF2 (seed for iter 4):** the tier-split reframe implies the advisor does both layers — what is the advisor's confidence story under that load? (from iteration 1, F4)\n+- **CF3 (seed for iter 3 + iter 4, NEW):** handoff is a *typed* closed-loop signal — strictly more informative than re-prompt (from iteration 2, obs-iter002-handoff-typed-signal). Iteration 3 should stress handoff as a primitive; iteration 4 should treat handoff as the input to a learned router.\n \n ## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n-**Iteration 2: Cross-domain analogies — the load-balancer health-check transfer (agenda #3).**\n-Iteration 1 stayed inside the routing domain. Iteration 2 deliberately imports a primitive from\n-outside routing entirely: weighted round-robin with health checks. Stress-test the lateral claim:\n-what if every mode had a runtime health score (recent success rate, recent token cost) and routing\n-weight adapted to it? Today every weight is static (`\"weight\": 4` everywhere). The load-balancer\n-analogy is the one most likely to surface a primitive routing doesn't have — OS scheduler, DNS,\n-and IP-router analogies collapse back to \"weighted selection\" and add less.\n+**Iteration 3: No-wrong-door / handoff routing + routing as dialogue (agenda #4 + #5).**\n+CF1 + CF3 converge here: if any mode could accept any request and then hand off (typed transfer),\n+does the keep-vs-null distinction dissolve? And does handoff supply the closed-loop signal F4 needs?\n+The lateral claim to stress-test: routing stops being \"pick the right mode upfront\" and becomes\n+\"any mode accepts, then types the transfer.\" The zero-signal case is not a silent default and not\n+a clarification dialog — it is a one-turn typed negotiation.\n \n ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n - Max iterations: 5 (hard stop; stopPolicy = max-iterations)\n - Convergence threshold: 0.05 (telemetry only; never triggers STOP)\n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/023-oob-glm-parallel/research/lineages/glm-oob/deep-research-strategy.md","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/023-oob-glm-parallel/research/lineages/glm-oob/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/023-oob-glm-parallel/research/lineages/glm-oob/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/023-oob-glm-parallel/research/lineages/glm-oob/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -84,48 +84,59 @@\n - **q1 — If Layer-1 routing were deleted entirely, what breaks vs improves?** (answered, iteration 1)\n   - Reframed: abolition is a **tier-split** (cold advisor decides `skill`; hot advisor-loaded vocab decides `mode`), not a deletion.\n   - Breaks: vocabulary centralisation kills per-skill authoring boundary; advisor becomes Layer-0+1 coupled; eager resource selection forced; `bundleRules` lose their encoding home.\n   - Improves: keep-vs-null disappears at the root; drift detectable at one file; `clarifying_question` already shipped becomes the single disambiguation surface.\n+- **q2 — Which routing primitive transfers from a non-routing domain, and at what cost?** (answered, iteration 2)\n+  - Four of five analogies (OS scheduler, IP longest-prefix, DNS hierarchy, receptionist) collapse to weighted-selection / bundleRules / defer — already shipped.\n+  - The genuine transfer is the **feedback channel** itself: closed-loop routing (emit `routeId`, record re-prompt). Load-balancer health-check and DNS TTL both pointed at it via different routes.\n+  - Health-score routing (F2) is the multi-release destination, not the immediate next step; F3's four costs (prompt-dependent state, grader cost, cold-start, Goodhart) make it non-trivial.\n \n ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n \n - **Reading the one shipped precedent (`_apply_deep_skill_routing_layer`)** made abolition answerable from evidence rather than speculation — it is the in-advisor hot tier already (iteration 1, F1).\n - **Pushing to the literal deletion** surfaced the tier-split reframe (F4) instead of stalling at \"null everyone.\"\n - **Stress-testing for second-order costs** (F2) produced four concrete breakages the run-1/run-2 study did not name.\n+- **Surveying all five analogies before committing to one** (iteration 2, F1) produced the negative-knowledge finding that four-of-five collapse; the one that does not (feedback channel) is itself a smaller primitive than its source analogy suggested.\n \n ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n \n - **Searching for a \"minimal deletion\"** — none exists. Keeping any of `routerPolicy` / `routerSignals` / `bundleRules` / `defaultResource` re-invents a Layer-1 router. The radical answer is all-or-nothing.\n+- **Trying to make the load-balancer transfer literal** (iter 2, F2) — the state-space explosion (F3.1) killed it as an immediate design.\n \n ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n \n-(none yet)\n+- **Static-selection analogies as a source of routing primitives.** OS scheduler, IP longest-prefix, receptionist — all collapse to today's `weight` / `vocabularyClasses` / `defer` / `bundleRules`. (iteration 2)\n \n ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n \n - **\"Set every `defaultMode` to null\" as abolition** — run-1/run-2 answer wearing a wig; abolition only counts if the four other routerPolicy fields are also deleted. (iteration 1)\n - **\"Generalise `_apply_deep_skill_routing_layer` verbatim\"** — lexical regex works for deep-loops only because their trigger vocab is small and stable; per-hub regex per domain is the distributed monolith in another shape. (iteration 1)\n+- **OS scheduler priority/preemption** — incoherent for one-shot routing; aging collapses to learned weights. (iteration 2)\n+- **IP longest-prefix match** — `vocabularyClasses` already is this. (iteration 2)\n+- **Receptionist \"ask, don't guess\"** — already shipped as `defer`. (iteration 2)\n+- **Full health-score routing (F2) as the immediate destination** — F3's four costs make it multi-release. The feedback-channel bridge (F4) is the productive next step. (iteration 2)\n \n ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n - Completed pivots: 0\n - Failed pivots: 0\n-- Saturated: none yet\n+- Saturated: static-selection analogies (4-of-5 agenda-#3 candidates exhausted)\n - Pivot lineage: none yet\n-- Remaining frontier: agenda items #2–#8 open; #1 explored (tier-split reframe)\n+- Remaining frontier: agenda #2, #4, #5, #6, #7, #8 open; #1 explored (tier-split); #3 explored (feedback channel)\n+- Promoted ideas: `idea-closed-loop-router` (1 observation, threshold 2 not yet met)\n \n ## 11. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n \n - **CF1 (seed for iter 3):** abolition makes the advisor the single deferrer, but advisor deferral is a *clarifying-question*, not a *handoff*. Is deferral the right primitive, or is handoff? (from iteration 1, obs-iter001-handoff-seed)\n - **CF2 (seed for iter 4):** the tier-split reframe implies the advisor does both layers — what is the advisor's confidence story under that load? (from iteration 1, F4)\n+- **CF3 (seed for iter 3 + iter 4, NEW):** handoff is a *typed* closed-loop signal — strictly more informative than re-prompt (from iteration 2, obs-iter002-handoff-typed-signal). Iteration 3 should stress handoff as a primitive; iteration 4 should treat handoff as the input to a learned router.\n \n ## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n-**Iteration 2: Cross-domain analogies — the load-balancer health-check transfer (agenda #3).**\n-Iteration 1 stayed inside the routing domain. Iteration 2 deliberately imports a primitive from\n-outside routing entirely: weighted round-robin with health checks. Stress-test the lateral claim:\n-what if every mode had a runtime health score (recent success rate, recent token cost) and routing\n-weight adapted to it? Today every weight is static (`\"weight\": 4` everywhere). The load-balancer\n-analogy is the one most likely to surface a primitive routing doesn't have — OS scheduler, DNS,\n-and IP-router analogies collapse back to \"weighted selection\" and add less.\n+**Iteration 3: No-wrong-door / handoff routing + routing as dialogue (agenda #4 + #5).**\n+CF1 + CF3 converge here: if any mode could accept any request and then hand off (typed transfer),\n+does the keep-vs-null distinction dissolve? And does handoff supply the closed-loop signal F4 needs?\n+The lateral claim to stress-test: routing stops being \"pick the right mode upfront\" and becomes\n+\"any mode accepts, then types the transfer.\" The zero-signal case is not a silent default and not\n+a clarification dialog — it is a one-turn typed negotiation.\n \n ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n - Max iterations: 5 (hard stop; stopPolicy = max-iterations)\n - Convergence threshold: 0.05 (telemetry only; never triggers STOP)\n","additions":21,"deletions":10},"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/023-oob-glm-parallel/research/lineages/glm-oob/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784348006422,"end":1784348006423}},"id":"prt_f736dd811001nea8BfCJE6Rl5Q","sessionID":"ses_08c9e6f24ffeeO094AtRujB8OZ","messageID":"msg_f736d471e001Lbg9xVvF9As9TL"}}
