{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784348519957,"sessionID":"ses_08c9e6f24ffeeO094AtRujB8OZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_7df049997c904255b5c034f4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"{\n  \"lineage\": \"glm-oob\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-glm-oob-1784347200936-r7aos1\",\n  \"topic\": \"Parent-hub routing, radical lateral rethinks (out-of-box GLM lineage)\",\n  \"openQuestions\": [],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    {\"id\": \"q1\", \"text\": \"If Layer-1 routing were deleted entirely, what breaks vs improves?\", \"status\": \"resolved\", \"iteration\": 1, \"resolution\": \"Abolition is a tier-split (cold advisor + hot advisor-loaded vocab), not a deletion.\"},\n    {\"id\": \"q2\", \"text\": \"Which routing primitive transfers from a non-routing domain, and at what cost?\", \"status\": \"resolved\", \"iteration\": 2, \"resolution\": \"Closed-loop feedback channel (smaller than health-check); four-of-five analogies collapse to weighted selection.\"},\n    {\"id\": \"q3\", \"text\": \"Does no-wrong-door/handoff dissolve the keep-vs-null distinction? At what cost?\", \"status\": \"resolved\", \"iteration\": 3, \"resolution\": \"Orthogonally yes; keep-vs-null becomes a cost inequality (one handoff vs one clarification turn), not a moral judgment.\"},\n    {\"id\": \"q4\", \"text\": \"Does confidence-first + learned routing make defaultMode meaningless?\", \"status\": \"resolved\", \"iteration\": 4, \"resolution\": \"Yes with handoff; the (T,R,P) decomposition subsumes defaultMode as one corner.\"},\n    {\"id\": \"q5\", \"text\": \"Is the INTENT_SIGNALS+RESOURCE_MAP scheme load-bearing or an accident?\", \"status\": \"resolved\", \"iteration\": 5, \"resolution\": \"Field-level conflation of three orthogonal concerns; minimal router = (T,R,P) + vocabulary table.\"}\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [\n    {\"id\": \"f1-handoff\", \"severity\": \"P1\", \"iteration\": 3, \"label\": \"Typed handoff needs routeId/fromMode/toMode/reason/evidence; current router has no handoff vocabulary\"},\n    {\"id\": \"f4-feedback\", \"severity\": \"P1\", \"iteration\": 2, \"label\": \"Genuine transfer is the feedback channel (closed-loop routing), smaller than health-check analogy\"},\n    {\"id\": \"f3-learn-assignment\", \"severity\": \"P1\", \"iteration\": 4, \"label\": \"Learn the vocabulary-to-mode assignment, not the weights (weights uniformly 4 = vestigial)\"},\n    {\"id\": \"f5-trp\", \"severity\": \"P1\", \"iteration\": 4, \"label\": \"Routing has three orthogonal knobs: Threshold (T), Recovery (R), Provenance (P); defaultMode is one corner\"},\n    {\"id\": \"f1-conflation\", \"severity\": \"P1\", \"iteration\": 5, \"label\": \"Smell named: routerPolicy fields conflate T/R/P across all 7 hubs\"},\n    {\"id\": \"f5-bug\", \"severity\": \"P1\", \"iteration\": 5, \"label\": \"defaultMode was never a design knob — it was a documented bug compensating for missing recovery primitive\"},\n    {\"id\": \"f2-minimal\", \"severity\": \"P1\", \"iteration\": 5, \"label\": \"Minimal router = (T,R,P) triple + vocabulary table; 6 routerPolicy fields deleted/relocated\"},\n    {\"id\": \"f1-precedent\", \"severity\": \"P1\", \"iteration\": 1, \"label\": \"_apply_deep_skill_routing_layer is the one shipped precedent for advisor-side mode pre-resolution\"},\n    {\"id\": \"f5-converge\", \"severity\": \"P1\", \"iteration\": 3, \"label\": \"Cross-iteration convergence: handoff is the typed substrate turning re-prompt into first-class closed-loop channel\"}\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n    {\"direction\": \"Set every defaultMode to null as abolition\", \"iteration\": 1},\n    {\"direction\": \"Generalise _apply_deep_skill_routing_layer verbatim\", \"iteration\": 1},\n    {\"direction\": \"OS scheduler priority/preemption as routing primitive\", \"iteration\": 2},\n    {\"direction\": \"IP longest-prefix match as routing primitive\", \"iteration\": 2},\n    {\"direction\": \"Receptionist ask-don't-guess as routing primitive\", \"iteration\": 2},\n    {\"direction\": \"Full health-score routing as immediate destination\", \"iteration\": 2},\n    {\"direction\": \"Any-mode-accepts without typed handoff vocabulary\", \"iteration\": 3},\n    {\"direction\": \"NWD as replacement for defaultMode:null\", \"iteration\": 3},\n    {\"direction\": \"Open-ended clarifying_question as zero-signal outcome\", \"iteration\": 3},\n    {\"direction\": \"Confidence-first routing without handoff\", \"iteration\": 4},\n    {\"direction\": \"Learn the weights\", \"iteration\": 4},\n    {\"direction\": \"Live in-path weight updates\", \"iteration\": 4},\n    {\"direction\": \"Keep defaultMode alongside (T,R,P)\", \"iteration\": 5},\n    {\"direction\": \"Mechanical codemod for (T,R,P) migration\", \"iteration\": 5},\n    {\"direction\": \"Shrink the vocabulary table too\", \"iteration\": 5}\n  ],\n  \"saturatedDirections\": [\n    \"static-selection analogies (iter 2)\",\n    \"confidence-first-without-handoff (iter 4)\",\n    \"static-Provenance plane generally (iter 4 F5)\"\n  ],\n  \"pivotLineage\": [],\n  \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n  \"promotedIdeas\": [\n    {\"ideaId\": \"idea-closed-loop-router\", \"observationCount\": 3, \"firstObservedRun\": 2, \"lastObservedRun\": 4, \"idea\": \"Closed-loop routing with typed handoff as the substrate\"},\n    {\"ideaId\": \"idea-minimal-router\", \"observationCount\": 1, \"firstObservedRun\": 5, \"lastObservedRun\": 5, \"idea\": \"Minimal router = (T,R,P) + vocabulary table\", \"note\": \"early-promoted as load-bearing synthesis claim\"}\n  ],\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n  \"graphNodes\": 15,\n  \"graphEdges\": 11\n}\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/023-oob-glm-parallel/research/lineages/glm-oob/findings-registry.json"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/023-oob-glm-parallel/research/lineages/glm-oob/findings-registry.json","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/023-oob-glm-parallel/research/lineages/glm-oob/findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1784348519953,"end":1784348519956}},"id":"prt_f7375ae0f001J8PEpz33VGWT9X","sessionID":"ses_08c9e6f24ffeeO094AtRujB8OZ","messageID":"msg_f737526fd001YqPEgE68xdSN2p"}}
